HEADWORD: Decalogue
<hw>Dec"a*logue</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧calogue</ets>, L. <ets>decalogus</ets>, fr. Gr.
<grk>de`ka</grk> ten + <grk>lo`gos</grk> speech, <grk>le`gw</grk> to
speak, to say. See <er>Ten</er>.]</ety> <def>The Ten Commandments or
precepts given by God to Moses on Mount Sinai, and originally written on
two tables of stone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

